Periodic update verification (30-second intervals).

Tests:
1) Periodic DV updates sent every 30 seconds
2) Updates occur even when topology is stable
3) Timing accuracy of periodic updates

Expected behavior:
- No topology changes occur during simulation
- DV updates still sent at regular 30-second intervals
- Expected update times: t ≈ 0, 30000, 60000, 90000, 120000, 150000, 180000

Verification:
- Parse simulator output for DV packet events
- Calculate time intervals between successive updates
- Intervals should be exactly 30000ms (±1ms for timing precision)

This test confirms periodic updates work independently of triggered
updates, as required by Section 4.2 of the specification.
